beware, I follow Jesus.
I also have an amazing wife @sav.labrant and 3 crazy kids.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Cole LaBrant on July 20, 2021 tagging @patty.othon, @everleighrose, and @posierayne. May be an image of 3 people, baby, people standing and indoor.

node.text: before I met Savannah, I didn’t really think much about being a dad. I was always the hopeless romantic type that just couldn’t wait to get married. I always assumed I wouldn’t start having kids until my 30s. I thank Savannah every day for throwing me into fatherhood with Everleigh. Had I not of fallen in love with a woman who already had a kid, I don’t know how eager I would’ve been to start my own family so soon. But meeting Savannah and Everleigh felt so natural. It was a no brainer and instantly all I wanted. I realized how different God’s plan for my life was, but also how much better it was going to be. My kids are my greatest treasures. I literally can’t imagine a day without them, much less my life. It’s crazy for me to think had I not of met Savannah, how much different my life would be. I’d be a 24 year old guy, likely still single with no kids... I’m sure to most guys, that sounds like the ideal situation.. But I sure am thankful for this life Gods surprised me with.🤍

node.text: happy anniversary to my one and only love. To the woman who made me a man. Who everyday makes me a better man. To the woman who somehow fell in love with me even when my hair was competing against hers. To the woman who’s aging like fine wine🤤... even tho I don’t really like wine.. I do really like you. And I really love you. A lot. Happy 1460 days of Holy Matrimony Honey💛

node.text: We’re currently in Vegas at Everleighs national dance competition. Vegas is very tiring with babies so I always volunteer for nap duty. The pic on the right is Posie 2 years ago napping with me in Vegas. The pic on the left is Zealand right now🖤

node.text: Savannah is the best mom in the world. I know everybody says that but Savannah actually is. She makes no selfish decision ever. Every decision she ever makes is filtered through what’s best for our kids. There’s nothing more attractive than how well she points our kids to Jesus. You’re patient, kind, caring, silly and intentional every day. I hope to be half the parent she is. Our kids don’t realize yet how blessed they are, but I do. I love you so much @sav.labrant

node.text: happy birthday to the most beautiful girl I’ve ever met. This is my 5th birthday celebrating you and after 5 years I’ve learned a lot about you. We spend just about every second of every day with each other and I’m amazed by your character. You’re real. You make me the proudest husband and I love showing you off. You’re selfless. So patient with our kids. The most fun and easy to get along with person I know. Your biggest desire is to help others in need and love your family well. You’re an inspiration to so many people, and everyone needs to know that Savannah is the best person to look up to. I’m so honored that my kids get to look up to you every day as a mom. It’s so easy to love you, and the more I get to know you the more blessed I feel that I get to call you my wife. I know God orchestrated me bumping in to you randomly 5 years ago and that’s the biggest miracle in my life. I love celebrating you and can never find enough good things to say about you. I love you, @sav.labrant

node.text: we got home late last night and this girl actually fell asleep on me. This is a big deal because Posie will not fall asleep in our bed. She loves her own bed and her own space. Any parent knows there’s few things better in life than your kid falling asleep on you🤍
